transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, my name is Jeanette Leslie, and I'm with my husband, Negad Garcia, we would like to

Speaker 2: cancel his medication, please, for this month.

Speaker 1: May I have the phone number associated with the account?

Speaker 2: I could give it to you right now.

Speaker 1: I'm the one that always ordering stuff for him.

Speaker 2: He tells me whatever, you know, so I'm just sending messages for him.

Speaker 1: But I don't know his number right here, so I don't save numbers.

Speaker 2: I'm sorry about that.

Speaker 1: I'm about to find out right now.

Speaker 2: I was honest, I didn't want to give it to him.

Speaker 1: Hold on.

Speaker 2: All right, I got it.

Speaker 1: 203.

Speaker 2: 203?

Speaker 1: Yep, 203-606-9100.

Speaker 2: You said 606?

Speaker 1: 203-606-9100.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I don't have any account under that number.

Speaker 1: Maybe use a different number?

Speaker 2: Sorry, my, 475-239-8844.

Speaker 1: Mr. Miguel Garcia?

Speaker 2: Who?

Speaker 1: For Mr. Miguel Garcia?

Speaker 2: Mr. Wolf Garcia.

Speaker 1: What is the name of your husband?

Speaker 2: Negad Garcia.

Speaker 1: Yes, that's what I said.

Speaker 2: You said you want to cancel the next refill.

Speaker 1: You want to pause and reorder as needed?

Speaker 2: He said he just don't have the money right now.

Speaker 1: So you're not going to get no refill and you can't just reorder later?

Speaker 2: Yes, he said he just don't got the funds right now for it.

Speaker 1: And he just want to postpone it.

Speaker 2: And if I need it, I'll refill.

Speaker 1: Three months off?

Speaker 2: What would he like?

Speaker 1: I don't know.

Speaker 2: He just told me to cancel it.

Speaker 1: That's all.

Speaker 2: Yeah, you don't have to cancel.

Speaker 1: We can pause the whole prescription so that way you can reorder.

Speaker 2: Because otherwise, when you're going to try to order 10 pills,

Speaker 1: the price is going to be doubled because they're going to have to get a new doctor's consultation.

Speaker 2: So I said pausing.

Speaker 1: So no monthly refill.

Speaker 2: And you can call to reorder, okay, as needed.

Speaker 1: Okay?

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: He just don't have the funds right now.

Speaker 2: So that's why he's telling me to cancel it.

Speaker 1: We're going to fix that for him so he's not going to receive anything.

Speaker 2: They're pausing for half a year and he can call to reorder, okay?

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Thank you so much.

Speaker 1: You're welcome.

Speaker 2: You have a good one.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: You too.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
